
This week I felt a bit more comfortable with things like making shapes. I feel like I'm just starting to touch the alphabet - not sure what so many
of the letters mean, or how to recall them again even once I have seen what they mean (do) in action, 
but I'm trying to let the process be what it is and not expect to understand already what I do not yet know or am only starting to
visualize.

One thing I'm working on is the way that works best for me to organize and recall information.
Since this feels like learning a language, I need to figure out
what kind of structure works best for me.

Overall, I feel like I know more than I did last week.


